➜留学文书写作CIC原则举例解析
http://www.sohu.com/a/418681856_490529	3204
<p>一篇留学文书应该具备哪些要素才能吸引招生官的眼球呢？我们可以从不同的角度和方面去思考这个问题。</p>
<p>首先我们可以问文书作者：你是否遵循了 <strong>“CIC”原则 </strong>，即：Clear 清晰、Interesting 有趣、Correct准确？</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p1.itc.cn/images01/20200916/89740bcc57354c1a9a7483b854bebd45.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p>其次我们也可以透过比较权威的网站，如commonapp.org 、 collegeboard.org或USNEWS.com去了解一下招生官，听听他们的偏好是什么。美国新闻周刊U.S. News在采访了缅因州的文理学院Bowdoin College 副校长兼招生办主任Whitney Soule后写道：</p>
<p>Soule says, “Students don't have to write about a major turning point in their essay… They can instead reflect on something from their day-to-day life that they find meaningful…”</p>
<p>For example, Soule says she remembers a strong essay in which a student wrote about being a sibling. The student talked about what his relationship with his younger brother was like at different points throughout his life.</p>
<p>There wasn't any big, dramatic moment that the story hinged on, Soule says. The essay just reflected on how the student and his brother had grown up and evolved in relation to one another.</p>
<p>"That was really personal," Soule says, "and it also demonstrated a person who could see himself in relationship to other people, which is a hugely important quality, particularly when we're building a community of people who are going to be living together and learning together."</p>            <div class="lookall-box">
<div class="lookall-shadow"></div>
<section class="lookall">
<a href="javascript:;" class="show-all" id="showMore">
